The Soviet Union conducted an undergroundnuclear test aimed at perfecting military technology, theofficial news agency Tass reported.    Tass said the test was carried out at 0120 gmt at theSemipalatinsk testing ground in Kazakhstan, Soviet CentralAsia.    It was the third Soviet underground blast since Moscowhalted an 18-month nuclear test moratorium last February,saying Washington's refusal to join the ban had forced it toresume testing. REUTER&#3;